In the United States, resolving a suit in a motion for summary judgment is <em>supposed</em> to be the same thing, where questions of law get resolved before the trial. &quot;Even if the facts are as the other side says they are, you're still within the law.&quot;<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Jan 13, 2015 8:01 am</p><hr />
