<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12237&amp;p=139118#p139118"><![CDATA[
If the facts in your case are not substantially different from the facts in another case, a lot of things can be dealt with in summary judgment, which is a lot cheaper than a trial. We don't know if N's lawyers sent a cease and desist to Color Dreams, but if so, Color Dreams' lawyers could have sent a reply mentioning cases N lost against other cart makers using CIC stun. &quot;In closing, we believe that proceeding with this legal action would not be the best use of your time and your client's money.&quot;<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Jan 11, 2015 8:33 pm</p><hr />
